<span class="s1">&lt;tr </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;row-odd&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;toc reference external&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;math.html#pygame.math.Vector3&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.math.Vector3</span><span class="s1">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;td&gt;</span><span class="s0">—</span><span class="s1">&lt;/td&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;td&gt;</span><span class="s0">a 3-Dimensional Vector</span><span class="s1">&lt;/td&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The pygame math module currently provides Vector classes in two and three</span>
<span class="s0">dimensions, </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Vector2</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">and </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Vector3</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">respectively.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">They support the following numerical operations: </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">vec+vec</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">vec-vec</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">,</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">vec*number</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">number*vec</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">vec/number</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">vec//number</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">vec+=vec</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">,</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">vec-=vec</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">vec*=number</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">vec/=number</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">vec//=number</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">All these operations will be performed elementwise.</span>
<span class="s0">In addition </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">vec*vec</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">will perform a scalar-product (a.k.a. dot-product).</span>
<span class="s0">If you want to multiply every element from vector v with every element from</span>
<span class="s0">vector w you can use the elementwise method: </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">v.elementwise()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">*</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">w</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The coordinates of a vector can be retrieved or set using attributes or</span>
<span class="s0">subscripts</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight-default notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">v</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;o&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">=</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;o&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Vector3</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;p&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>

<span class="s0">This value acts as a numerical margin in various methods to account for floating point</span>
<span class="s0">arithmetic errors. <span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;nb&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">print</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;p&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">v</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;o&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">==</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">u</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;p&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;c1&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0"># </span><span class="s4">&amp;gt;&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">False</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">You'll probably never have to change </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">epsilon</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">from the default value, but in rare situations you might</span>
<span class="s0">find that either the margin is too large or too small, in which case changing </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">epsilon</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">slightly</span>
<span class="s0">might help you out.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</span><span class="s0">Experimental:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/strong&gt; </span><span class="s0">feature still in development available for testing and feedback. It may change.</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference external&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;https://github.com/pygame/pygame/pull/2929&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Please leave move_towards feedback with authors</span><span class="s1">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Returns a Vector which is moved towards the given Vector by a given</span>
<span class="s0">distance and does not overshoot past its target Vector.</span>
<span class="s0">The first parameter determines the target Vector, while the second</span>
<span class="s0">parameter determines the delta distance. If the distance is in the</span>
<span class="s0">negatives, then it will move away from the target Vector.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;summaryline&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">moves the vector toward its target at a given distance.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">move_towards_ip(Vector3, float) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">None</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</span><span class="s0">Experimental:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/strong&gt; </span><span class="s0">feature still in development available for testing and feedback. It may change.</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference external&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;https://github.com/pygame/pygame/pull/2929&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Please leave move_towards_ip feedback with authors</span><span class="s1">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Moves itself toward the given Vector at a given distance and does not</span>
<span class="s0">overshoot past its target Vector.</span>
<span class="s0">The first parameter determines the target Vector, while the second</span>
<span class="s0">parameter determines the delta distance. If the distance is in the</span>
<span class="s0">negatives, then it will move away from the target Vector.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
